Corrected inflated number of "hundreds of thousands" to "tens of thousands" for better accuracy. Furth 1999, p. 229 "conservatively estimates" that of 120,000 rescue attempts, only 50,000 self-identified Jews and 20,000 non-self-identifying Jews survived. Piotrowski 1997, p. 117 doesn't provide a total estimate, but only mentions 50,000 "forged Aryan documents" and 4,000 that received financial support. No matter how you look at it "hundreds of thousands" of aided/concealed is overinflated.
